<!-- <title>Previo a la unidad</title> -->
<title>Exploración</title>
<!-- <title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="graVV-uniYY-secZZ" text="title"/></title> -->
<!-- <title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="lec-VVVVVV" text="title"/></title> -->

<statement>
  <p>¿En qué se parecen la tira de fracciones y la recta numérica? ¿En qué son diferentes?</p>
  <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151744">
    <shortdescription>Diagram. Rectangle partitioned into 8 equal parts, each labeled one eighth.</shortdescription>
  </image>
  <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151745">
    <shortdescription>Number line. Scale 0 to 1 by eighths. Evenly spaced tick marks. First tick mark, 0. Last tick mark, 1.</shortdescription>
  </image>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[++++++++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Sample responses: The fraction strip and number line are both divided into 8 equal pieces and they both are labeled using eighths. The fraction strip only shows <m>\frac{1}{8}</m> pieces, it does not show <m>\frac{2}{8}</m> or <m>\frac{3}{8}</m>. Also the <m>\frac{1}{8}</m> labels are in the middle of the rectangles. On the number line, the labels are for the tick marks or points on the number line.</p>
</solution>

</exercise>
